Package com.pb.sawdust.tabledata

Provides classes for dealing with data tables.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataColumn<T>
    The DataColumn interface provides a framework through which columns of a DataTable can be accessed.
    DataRow
    The DataRow interface provides a framework through which rows of a DataTable can be accessed.
    DataSet<T extends DataTable>
    The DataSet interface provides a framework to hold a number of DataTables.
    DataTable
    The DataTable interface provides a basic framework for a structure holding similarly structured rows of data.
    TableIndex<I>
    A TableIndex object holds a mapping from the value(s) of one or more columns to the rows in a data table which contain those values.
    TableKey<K>
    A TableKey object is a specialized TableIndex which maps a single column's values uniquely to a data table's rows.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDataColumn<T>
    The AbstractDataRow class provides a skeletal version of DataColumn which implements as many methods as possible, reducing the coding burden on the implementing user.
    AbstractDataRow
    The AbstractDataRow class provides a skeletal version of DataRow which implements as many methods as possible, reducing the coding burden on the implementing user.
    AbstractDataSet<T extends DataTable>
    The AbstractDataSet provides a skeletal implementation of DataSet which lowers the implementation bar for developers.
    AbstractDataTable
    The AbstractDataTable class provides a skeletal version of DataTable which implements as many methods as possible, reducing the coding burden on the implementing user.
    AbstractDataTable.DataTablePartition
    The DataTablePartition class provides a basic data table partition which can be used to fulfill the DataTable.getTablePartition(int,int) method.
    AbstractTableIndex<I,K>
    The AbstractTableIndex class provides a skeletal version of TableIndex which reduces the coding burden on the implementing user.
    AbstractTableKey<K>
    The AbstractTableKey class provides a skeletal version of TableKey which reduces the coding burden on the implementing user.
    BooleanDataColumn
    The BooleanDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.BOOLEAN.
    ByteDataColumn
    The ByteDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.BYTE.
    DoubleDataColumn
    The DoubleDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.DOUBLE.
    FloatDataColumn
    The FloatDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.FLOAT.
    FrozenTableKey<K>
    The FrozenTableKey is an immutable TableKey.
    IntegerDataColumn
    The IntegerDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.INT.
    LongDataColumn
    The LongDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.LONG.
    ShortDataColumn
    The ShortDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.SHORT.
    StringDataColumn
    The StringDataColumn provides a wrapper class for DataColumns of the type DataType.STRING.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    TableDataException
    The TableDataException class provides a lightweight, non-checked exception specific to the TableData and associated packages.
